<paragraph blockId="19.[264,1323,1054,1240]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis box="[264,366,1054,1079]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Remarks</emphasis>
: 
<bibRefCitation author="Kitbamroong" box="[387,789,1054,1080]" pageId="19" pageNumber="48" refString="Kitbamroong, N. A. &amp; Freytag, P. H. (1978) The species of the genus Scaphoideus (Homoptera: Cicadellidae) found in Thailand, with descriptions of new species. Pacific Insects, 18, 19 - 31." type="journal article" year="1978">
Kitbamroong and Freytag (
<number box="[719,780,1054,1080]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="1978.0">1978</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
have adequately described this species and also recorded the species from 
<collectingCountry box="[636,700,1094,1120]" name="India" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">India</collectingCountry>
. However, no specimens of this species were examined during the study. This species can be confused with 
<emphasis box="[936,1071,1134,1159]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<taxonomicName box="[936,1067,1134,1159]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="morosus">S. morosus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
from which it differs in having paraphyses long, robust, U­shaped, and converging with a small thin seta on each side terminally.
</paragraph>
